<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-01-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/626.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the First
                                    Central American Conference</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-01-13"><hi rend="italic">January 13,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Delegates Tegucigalpa Conference thankfully acknowedge your excellency’s
                            good offices and take pleasure in announcing to you that they are
                            continuing their labors.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Aguirre Munoz.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>